    <div id="bios" style="display:none">
      <p><strong>Josh Izenberg: Director/Producer</strong></p>
      <p>Josh hails from Ann Arbor, where he earned a degree in Screenwriting from the University of Michigan. He's since worked as a copywriter, a cab driver, and a carpenter. SLOMO is his first documentary.</p>
      <br>
      <p><strong>Amanda Micheli: Producer</strong></p>
      <p>Amanda is an Oscar-nominated filmmaker and a celebrated cinematographer. Her first film, JUST FOR THE RIDE, won a student Oscar and IDA Award. DOUBLE DARE, which followed the struggles of two Hollywood stuntwomen, premiered at Toronto and was an audience favorite at festivals worldwide. LA CORONA premiered at Sundance and won an Oscar nod before airing on HBO, and is currently in development for adaptation into a fiction feature. Most recently, she directed THE SAVE for ESPN and ONE NATION UNDER DOG for HBO. Her other credits include THIN, CAT DANCERS, “30 Days,” and MY FLESH AND BLOOD.</p>
      <br>
      <p><strong>Traci Loth: Editor</strong></p>
      <p>Traci is a San Francisco-based editor with over a decade of experience in documentary and commercial work for television and film. She cut the award-winning documentary Row Hard, No Excuses. Her corporate clients include Apple, Nike, Yahoo!, and Adobe. Most recently, she was editor for Aerial America (Smithsonian Channel) and One Nation Under Dog (HBO). Currently she is cutting a 60-min feature for ESPN's Nine for IX series.</p>
      <br>
      <p><strong>Wynn Padula: Cinematographer/Co-Producer</strong></p>
      <p>Wynn received his M.F.A. in both Directing and Cinematography from the UCLA School of Theater, Film and Television in 2007, where he had the opportunity to learn from some of the world's top cinematographers including Roger Deakins and Janusz Kaminski. Wynn has since produced and shot many festival-winning films including "The Breeze Team" (2nd Place winner, Canadian International Film Festival), "Rainbow Klansmen" (Mill Valley Film Festival), "Felicia's House" and "Lynx" (Best Short Film, Wild & Scenic Film Festival). Before becoming a professional director of photography, Wynn worked in development under the legendary producer Roger Corman.</p>
      <br>
      <p><strong>Nate Sloan: original music</strong></p>
      <p>Nate studies musicology at Stanford University, teaches jazz history at the Berkeley Jazz Institute, and performs as one-half of the freak-folk duo Sly Boots. He has also written music and lyrics for two musicals, Leavittsburg, OH (2009, Brown University) and Baz and Me (2010, Playwrights' Rep). Slomo is his first film score.</p>
      <br>
      <p><strong>Nick Gage: original music</strong></p>
      <p>Nick is a Chicago based Songwriter/multi-instrumentalist. Many of his songs have appeared on NPR through local affiliate WBEZ. 2012 brought about his debut musical "Holy Musical B@man!" with Team StarKid. He is currently music directing at Second City.</p>
